ul.li:
The Main toolbar which contains buttons for global application operation as there are:


Create a new document;

Open;

Save;

Compute the number of formal concepts;

Compute the concept lattice;

Perform the attribute exploration;

Calculate the Duquenne-Guigues set of implications;

Calculate association rules;

additionally we have to mention the combo box which allows to select the update mode for the document components that are computed from the formal context (concept lattice, set of implications and association rules). Currently two update modes are supported. Those are re-computation of the affected components or clear them. The latter mode is recommended when changing the context reasonably. After realisation of those changes the appropriate operations can be reoptained for the new context.
In the case of many changes the other option would cause a re-computation for every single alteration of the context and may lead to computational expenses if the context is big or dense.
